does anyone remember the floppy disk days how horrible were those we sure have come along way ok i remember pre photocopier days when if you wanted an exact duplicate of a document you had to use carbon paper and hope you didn't make too many mistakes there were special erasers just to use on the carbon copy if you did make mistakes i also remember life before tv gasp i remember most people had party lines telephone that is several households shared one telephone line and each household had it's own distinctive ring you weren't supposed to pick up someone else's ring but people did and just listened in the other folks on your party line were usually strangers and might not even live near you unless you were wealthy most families only owned one car if you were lucky people could smoke anywhere and everywhere even in the movie theaters everyone got dressed up when they went shopping because all the department stores were downtown you could actually buy things for a penny you could stick a letter in the mailbox without a stamp and the postal delivery person would collect the postage when he delivered it i even remember when santa monica california was mainly still just sand dunes and a lot of la was still vacant land and what's even more impressive my parents remember things even before all of this Postage stamp United States Postal Service Typewriter Royal Mail Photocopying Surveillance Frank Herbert Stamp collecting Santa Claus Gramophone record Post office Penny Black Santa Monica, California Philately Apple Open Collaboration Environment Autograph Beverly Hills, California Copy protection The Marshall Mathers LP Killian documents Roswell UFO incident Little Britain Medical prescription Atchison, Topeka and Santa Fe Railway Atari 8-bit family E-mail Password Theory of conduct Social rule The Star Wars Holiday Special Floppy disk Dennis Rader Microeconomics Retronym Postage stamps and postal history of the United States George Lucas One-time pad Humphrey Bogart Shagg